## 5. Summary Assessment

| Category | Rating | Notes |
|----------|--------|-------|
| **Architecture** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | Clean separation, serverless-ready, well-structured monorepo |
| **API Logic** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | Stats engine, H2H rankings, bracket seeding all work correctly |
| **Security** | ⭐⭐ | No auth on API routes — the biggest gap in the project |
| **Design System** | ⭐⭐⭐ | Good token system, but inconsistent inline vs class usage |
| **Mobile Responsiveness** | ⭐⭐⭐⭐ | Good use of `clamp()`, responsive grids, swipeable panels |
| **Code Quality** | ⭐⭐⭐ | Some dead code and duplication, but generally readable |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The project is **functionally solid** — the tournament logic, rankings, bracket system, and canvas export all work well. The two biggest areas for improvement are **API security** (adding real auth middleware) and **design consistency** (converting the remaining inline styles to CSS classes).
